This certificate course may be helpful for someone who is wondering if they would like to take their career in this direction. The certification is not substantial enough to provide an experienced person with validation of their abilities, fill in gaps in experience towards gaining a promotion, or new knowledge, skills, and abilities a novice could use to confidently apply for a HR Analyst job. There is an opportunity for UCI to, at a minimum, define what the certificate might convey to employers as well as learners, clean up their misspellings and punctuation, and review their quiz answers and feedback for accuracy and clarity.

T‚Äãhe course length was good. But I feel the "readings" could've been skipped or reduced. The lecture content could've been divided into 2-3 parts perhaps, just so everything isn't pushed into 1 video. Additionally, I found the lectures to be not very helpful The lecturer missed some points and did not explain the concepts properly. The Pros: The course was simple to navigate. The slides were easy to understand and didn't have a bunch of extra unnecessary info. I love that this course was easily attainable in a short amount of time, as I'm a person in the middle of a career change.The Cons: This is probably preference, but the videos were a bit longer than other courses I've taken. Not by much, they were less than 20 mins per video. I find that it tricks the mind if you chop those videos in half to more chewable chunks (but that's just me). The questions at times were a bit difficult to understand, particularly the ones that ask the question in reverse (ie "what is NOT an example of...). And some of the answers were so similar that you think it could be either, or a couple of the answers could BE the correct answer (if you're someone like me, who is trying to pick the correct answer, and saying in your head "well technically..."). When you take the quiz, they give you feedback on each answer, but sometimes after reading the feedback on the answers you missed, you're still sitting there like, "ok, what's the answer then?" And a couple of them, I still don't know the answer to. If you have to retake the test, don't blaze through it, because although the questions were in the same order, the answer order was switched up, so pay attention to that.Tips: Read the articles/watch the video she gives you as the supplemental information! I thought that it was just extra reading that you could ALSO read in your leisure time, but a good deal of the answers are in those articles! And they actually weren't that bad of articles, very simple to get through that you can read in like 5 mins.
